A Utility to Check Configuration Files
---------------------------------------

On macOS and Linux use gcc to build the binary:

> gcc -o checkConfigurationFile -I ../../firmware/inc/ checkConfigurationFile.c ../../firmware/src/configParser.c 

On Windows use the 'x64_x86 Cross Tools Command Prompt' to build the 32-bit binary:

> cl /I ../../firmware/inc/ checkConfigurationFile.c ../../firmware/src/configParser.c /link /out:checkConfigurationFile.exe

